# Cerebrum - Secure Neural Data Sharing

[![Flow Blockchain](https://img.shields.io/badge/Blockchain-Flow-00EF8B?style=flat-square)](https://flow.com/)
[![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/Frontend-React%2018-61DAFB?style=flat-square)](https://reactjs.org/)
[![Vite](https://img.shields.io/badge/Build%20Tool-Vite-646CFF?style=flat-square)](https://vitejs.dev/)
[![TailwindCSS](https://img.shields.io/badge/Styling-TailwindCSS-38B2AC?style=flat-square)](https://tailwindcss.com/)
[![Lit Protocol](https://img.shields.io/badge/Access%20Control-Lit%20Protocol-654EA3?style=flat-square)](https://litprotocol.com/)
[![Storacha](https://img.shields.io/badge/Storage-Storacha%2FFilecoin-0A9F51?style=flat-square)](https://storacha.web3.storage/)

A secure web application for privacy-preserving neurotechnology data sharing. Upload neural datasets securely, encrypt them client-side, store them on decentralized storage (Storacha/Filecoin), and control access through wallet-based permissions with Lit Protocol. Grant or revoke access to other researchers while maintaining complete data sovereignty.

## 🌐 Live Deployment

The application is deployed and accessible at the provided deployment URL.

### Key Deployment Information
- Uses Flow Testnet for wallet authentication
- Data encrypted with Lit Protocol before storage
- Files stored on Storacha (Web3.Storage) backed by Filecoin
## Key Features

### Core Functionality
- **Secure Upload**: Streamlined neural data file upload with validation and preview
- **Client-Side Encryption**: All data encrypted with Lit Protocol before transmission
- **Decentralized Storage**: Files stored on Storacha/Filecoin for permanent, censorship-resistant access
- **Wallet Authentication**: Flow wallet integration for secure user authentication
- **Access Control**: Grant and revoke access to specific wallet addresses with optional expiry
- **Permission Management**: Fine-grained control over who can access your neural datasets

### Data Management
- **Dashboard**: View all uploaded datasets with metadata and status badges
- **Activity Tracking**: Monitor who accessed your data and when
- **Data Preview**: View parsed neural data before encryption and upload
- **Revoke Access**: Instantly revoke permissions to previously-granted wallets
- **Access Logs**: Comprehensive activity history showing all access attempts

### User Experience
- **Modern Interface**: Clean, responsive design built with React 18 and TailwindCSS
- **Wallet Integration**: Seamless Flow wallet connection and management
- **Background Animations**: Engaging particle animations for visual appeal
- **Mobile Responsive**: Optimized experience across desktop and mobile devices
- **Toast Notifications**: Clear feedback on all user actions and errors

## Technical Architecture

### Frontend Application Structure
```
src/
├── components/                 # React UI components
│   ├── LandingPage.jsx        # Main landing page
│   ├── VaultDashboard.jsx     # User dashboard
│   ├── UploadPage.jsx         # File upload interface
│   ├── ConsentPage.jsx        # Access permission management
│   ├── AccessPage.jsx         # Access verification and decryption
│   ├── AccessLogPage.jsx      # Activity history and logs
│   ├── MetricsPage.jsx        # Usage analytics
│   ├── Navbar.jsx             # Navigation component
│   ├── FlowConnectGate.jsx    # Wallet authentication gate
│   ├── ErrorBoundary.jsx      # Error handling
│   ├── BackgroundParticles.jsx # Visual background effects
│   ├── analytics/             # Analytics components
│   │   └── [chart components]
│   ├── management/            # Dashboard management components
│   │   └── [admin components]
│   └── modals/                # Modal dialogs
│       ├── BaseModal.tsx
│       ├── DepositModal.tsx
│       └── [other modals]
├── context/                   # React context
│   └── WalletContext.jsx      # Wallet state management
├── services/                  # Business logic
│   ├── litAccess.js          # Lit Protocol integration
│   ├── storachaClient.js     # Storacha/Filecoin integration
│   ├── cryptoAesGcm.js       # Encryption utilities
│   ├── metadataIndex.js      # Metadata management
│   └── env.js                # Environment configuration
├── main.jsx                  # React entry point
├── App.jsx                   # Main app component
└── index.css                 # Global styles
```

### External Services Integration
- **Flow Wallet**: User authentication and account management
- **Lit Protocol**: Client-side encryption and decryption operations
- **Storacha/Web3.Storage**: Decentralized file storage (Filecoin-backed)
- **ICLighthouse**: Analytics and metrics tracking (optional)

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- **Node.js**: Version 16.0.0 or higher
- **npm**: Version 7.0.0 or higher
- **Git**: For version control
- **Flow Wallet**: Browser extension or account at flow.com
- **Testnet FLOW tokens**: For transaction fees (if testing on testnet)

### Installation and Setup

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/cerebrum.git
   cd Cerebrum
   ```

2. **Install dependencies:**
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

3. **Set up environment variables:**
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env.local
   ```
   
   Update `.env.local` with your configuration:
   ```env
   VITE_FLOW_ACCESS_NODE=https://rest-testnet.onflow.org
   VITE_FLOW_DISCOVERY_WALLET=https://flow-wallet-testnet.blocto.app/authn
   VITE_LIT_CHAIN=filecoinTestnet
   VITE_WEB3_STORAGE_TOKEN=your_web3_storage_token
   VITE_FCL_NETWORK=testnet
   ```

4. **Start the development server:**
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

5. **Access the application:**
   - **Frontend**: http://localhost:5173
   - Default port may vary; check terminal output

### Usage Workflow

1. **Connect Your Wallet**
   - Click "Connect Wallet" on the landing page
   - Approve the Flow Wallet connection
   - Wallet address will appear in the navbar

2. **Upload Neural Data**
   - Navigate to Dashboard → Upload
   - Select a JSON neural data file
   - Preview the parsed data
   - Click "Encrypt & Upload"
   - System encrypts with Lit Protocol and stores on Storacha

3. **Grant Access**
   - In Dashboard, select a dataset
   - Click "Manage Consent"
   - Enter a wallet address to grant access
   - Optionally set expiry date
   - Click "Grant Access"

4. **Verify Access (as Recipient)**
   - Connect as the recipient wallet
   - Navigate to Access page
   - Select the shared dataset
   - System decrypts with Lit Protocol if authorized
   - View or download decrypted data

5. **Revoke Access**
   - Return to your dataset
   - Click "Revoke" next to the wallet address
   - Access immediately denied for that wallet
   - Activity log shows revocation event

## Development

### Environment Configuration

**Local Development** (`.env.local`):
```env
VITE_FLOW_ACCESS_NODE=https://rest-testnet.onflow.org
VITE_FLOW_DISCOVERY_WALLET=https://flow-wallet-testnet.blocto.app/authn
VITE_LIT_CHAIN=filecoinTestnet
VITE_WEB3_STORAGE_TOKEN=your_token_here
VITE_FCL_NETWORK=testnet
NODE_ENV=development
```

**Production** (`.env.production`):
```env
VITE_FLOW_ACCESS_NODE=https://rest-mainnet.onflow.org
VITE_FLOW_DISCOVERY_WALLET=https://flow-wallet.blocto.app/authn
VITE_LIT_CHAIN=filecoinMainnet
VITE_WEB3_STORAGE_TOKEN=your_production_token
VITE_FCL_NETWORK=mainnet
NODE_ENV=production
VITE_BUILD_MODE=production
```

### Essential Development Commands

```bash
# Development
npm run dev                      # Start development server (port 5173)
npm run build                    # Build for production
npm run format                   # Format code with Prettier
npm test                         # Run tests with Vitest
npm run demo:e2e                # Run E2E demo script

# Cleaning
npm run clean:cache             # Clear build cache
npm run dev:clean               # Clean cache and start dev server
```

### Project Scripts

All available npm scripts from `package.json`:
- `npm run dev` - Start Vite dev server on port 5173
- `npm run dev:clean` - Clean cache and start dev
- `npm run clean:cache` - Remove vite cache and temp files
- `npm run setup` - Install dependencies
- `npm run start` - Start Vite server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run format` - Format code with Prettier
- `npm test` - Run Vitest tests
- `npm run demo:e2e` - Run end-to-end demo

### Configuration Files

Key configuration files in the project:
- `vite.config.js`: Build tool configuration
- `tailwind.config.js`: Styling framework setup
- `postcss.config.cjs`: CSS processing
- `tsconfig.json`: TypeScript configuration
- `package.json`: Dependencies and scripts
- `.env.local`: Local environment variables
- `.env.production`: Production environment variables

## Security Features

- **Client-Side Encryption**: All data encrypted with Lit Protocol before transmission—server never sees plaintext
- **Wallet Authentication**: Flow Wallet integration ensures secure, decentralized identity
- **Decentralized Storage**: Files stored on Filecoin via Storacha—no single point of failure
- **Access Control**: Smart contract-based permissions using Lit Protocol conditions
- **Revocable Access**: Instant revocation of permissions without data re-encryption
- **Activity Audit Trail**: Complete log of all access attempts and management actions

